annotationA: Elongation factor 1-gamma; Ef1gamma associates with other EF1 subunits (alpha/beta/delta). It binds tubulin and Doa protein kinase, which in turns phosphorylates Ef1gamma. Ef1gamma regulates organelle movement along microtubules
annotationB: T-complex chaperonin 5, isoform A; Molecular chaperone; assists the folding of proteins upon ATP hydrolysis
